                  "content": "\u003cem\u003eE pluribus unum\u003c/em\u003e, a Latin phrase found on all U.S. coins, means “we are one people.”"
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "Persons of all races and ethnicities who commit a particular crime receive the same sentence for that crime."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "The United States has historically granted citizenship to everyone who lives within our national boundaries."
                },
                {
